sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1705
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a composite part built from part M1704 (promoter+RBS+scrR+terminator) and part M1703 (promoter+RBS+inulosucrase+RBS+scrT+terminator). With this combination it is now a complete operon for the increased uptake of sucrose into the cell and conversion of sucrose to inulin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: S. Ivan Bartlett
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Registry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: N/A

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1703
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inulosucrase and scrT sucrose transport protein composite part
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: inulosucrase enzyme and sucrose transporter scrT downstream of sucrose regulated promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jonathan L. Wood
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: composite part
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: codon optimization

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1704
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: this is the composite part with promoter, RBS, ScrR and terminator for Inulosucrase to digest fructose into inulin, which will not be absorbed by human body.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Qifei Li
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Composite part
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_M1695 is ScrR promoter BBa_M1694 RBS BBa_M1696 ScrR BBa_M1700 terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1701
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: ScrR regulatory promoter and a RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the promoter to which binds ScrR to regulate the transcription of a gene. We also added onto the end a RBS from Lactobacillus Sakei as identified on the NCBI website.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Benjamin L Hanks
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This is a combination of part M1696 and M1694
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We needed a promoter that ScrR regulates and a RBS that works in Lactobacillus, so we had to seek those out.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1695
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This promoter is for the bacteria Lactobacillus agilis, it promotes for the protein ScrR at high efficiency.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tiffany Hansen
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Promoter for ScrR in Lactobacillus agilis as identified in NCBI gene database.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Needed to work in Lactobacillus.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1694
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This ribosome binding site initiates translation for the bacteria Lactobacillus.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tiffany Hansen
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Ribosome binding site for ScrR in Lactobacillus sakei subsp. sakei as identified in NCBI gene database.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It needed to initiate for Lactobacillus.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1696
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: scrR LacI family sucrose operon repressor
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: ScrR is in the LacI family for operon repression. It negatively regulates by binding as a repressor to the promoter. In the presence of sucrose it is deactivated and transcription can occur.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Benjamin L Hanks
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: scrR sequence found in Lactobacillus sakei subsp. sakei as identified in NCBI gene database
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Checked for RE sites. Also had to find how it is promoted because it appears to be immediatly downstream from the gene it regulates

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1700
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A transcription terminator native to L. johnsonii NCC 533. This terminator originally exists downstream of the rpsR coding sequence. It was used in our project downstream from scrT to terminate transcription. This terminator has a deltaG of -12.33.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: S. Ivan Bartlett
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From L. johnsonii derived by use of the Webgester DB. http://pallab.serc.iisc.ernet.in/gester/65481116/index.html
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence was not altered in any way since it was to be used in L. johnsonii and that is the native organism from which it was derived.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1699
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This gene sequence codes for the ScrT protein which serves as a symporter for sucrose into the cell. The sequence is originally from [Bifidobacterium animalis subsp. lactis]. The sequence is normally a part of a gene cluster containing scrT, scrP, and scrR. Only scrT was used specifically from these gene cluster in our project to increase the uptake of sucrose by the cell. The sequence present in this part has been optimized for use in Lactobacillus johnsonii.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: S. Ivan Bartlett
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/22550282
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence was put into DNA 2.0's Gene Designer software to optimize its G-C content for use in Lactobacillus Johnsonii. Also it was checked for comparability with standard 10 restriction enzymes. The sequence here does not contain any restriction site conflicts with standard 10.
